I tried to upload Crimson tide 3 times here and ''Torrent already exist in the system'' appears.What's wrong with the site ??

@kriss..  that message means that the hash value already exists in the database. if you delete a torrent yourself, the hash stays and only a mod can remove it. thats so that virus torrents can't be reuploaded.
you can create a new torrent file so the hash value changes or get a mod to delete it from the database.

atm though, there seems to be a bug. have a read here:
